      <lg xml:id="TolE0237">
<l>iṉṟi yeṉṉum viṉaiyeñ ciṟuti</l>
<l>niṉṟa vikara mukara māta</l>
<l>ṟoṉṟiyaṉ maruṅkiṟ ceyyuḷu ḷurittē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The <foreign xml:lang="ta">i</foreign> standing at the end of the gerund <foreign xml:lang="ta">iṉṟi</foreign></l>
<l>is changed to <foreign xml:lang="ta">u</foreign></l>
<l>in the old traditional poetry.<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">toṉṟiyal maruṅkiṉ cevyuḷuḷ.</foreign> Accord. to
          commentators (and actual usage) this applies also to <foreign xml:lang="ta">aṉṟi &gt; aṉṟu.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
